{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"sugot-romuz","disc":"fifas-movuv","kind":"argument","text":"Reject cyclic preference at assert-time (it is not a strict order anyway); closure over an acyclic relation never collapses","author":"Theorist"},"source":"Theorist","valid_start":1780947537}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"hozag-bodah","disc":"fifas-movuv","kind":"argument","text":"Derived preferences are auditable: every edge is a logged move and 'why' shows the closure chain, so nothing is hidden","author":"Proposer"},"source":"Proposer","valid_start":1780947504}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"hovup-kafog","disc":"fifas-movuv","kind":"argument","text":"Without closure the preference relation is not a strict partial order; defeat-modulo-preference loses its well-foundedness guarantee","author":"Theorist"},"source":"Theorist","valid_start":1780947504}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"hovub-mafam","disc":"fifas-movuv","kind":"argument","text":"Preference cycles (A\u003eB\u003eC\u003eA) close to all-prefer-all: every dispute silently self-defeats","author":"Skeptic"},"source":"Skeptic","valid_start":1780947504}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"hovol-lanor","disc":"fifas-movuv","kind":"argument","text":"Closure manufactures defeats nobody stated: a position loses to a preference the author never asserted","author":"Skeptic"},"source":"Skeptic","valid_start":1780947504}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fifop-puron","disc":"fifas-movuv","kind":"position","text":"Transitively close preference: derive A\u003eC from A\u003eB and B\u003eC","author":"Proposer"},"source":"Proposer","valid_start":1780947494}
{"relation":"dlktk/node","args":{"id":"fifof-johun","disc":"fifas-movuv","kind":"position","text":"Explicit edges only: preference means exactly the pairs stated, no closure","author":"Proposer"},"source":"Proposer","valid_start":1780947494}
